Date: Mon, 10 Sep 2007 14:02:57 +0200
From: Laurent Vivier <>
Subject: [RESEND]PATCH 2/4] Introduce a new fields "gtime" and "cgtime" in task_struct and signal_struct
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2007/9/10/91

[PATCH 2/4] like for cpustat, introduce the "gtime" (guest time of the task) and
"cgtime" (guest time of the task children) fields for the
tasks. Modify signal_struct and task_struct. Modify /proc/<pid>/stat to display
these new fields.
Signed-off-by: Laurent Vivier <Laurent.Vivier@bull.net>
-- 
------------- Laurent.Vivier@bull.net  --------------
          "Software is hard" - Donald Knuth
